# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PREFERRED: download a ready-to-run install script from the coordinator
# admin portal and skip this file entirely.
#
#     https://<coordinator>/admin/install/<client-id>.sh    # bash
#     https://<coordinator>/admin/install/<client-id>.ps1   # PowerShell
#
# The script ships with the coordinator URL, client id, and client
# secret already baked in, pulls ghcr.io/sharpninja/bitnetsharp-worker,
# and runs it with the same hardened options as docker-compose.
#
# Use this .env only when you want to run multiple worker replicas via
# `docker compose up --scale worker=N`.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to `.env` next to docker-compose.yml and fill in the values
# before running `docker compose up`. Never commit the real `.env` —
# it contains the OAuth client secret for this worker.

# ── required ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BITNET_COORDINATOR_URL=https://bitnet-coord.ngrok.app/
BITNET_CLIENT_ID=worker-alpha
BITNET_CLIENT_SECRET=change-me-from-the-coordinator-admin-page

# ── optional ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BITNET_WORKER_NAME=worker-a
# BITNET_CPU_THREADS=8
# BITNET_HEARTBEAT_SECONDS=30
# BITNET_SHUTDOWN_SECONDS=30
# BITNET_LOG_LEVEL=info
